^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  1) # Getting Started with Create React App
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  2) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  3) This project was bootstrapped with [Create React App](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app).
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  4) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  5) ## Available Scripts
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  6) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  7) In the project directory, you can run:
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  8) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  9) ### `npm start`
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 10) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 11) Runs the app in the development mode.\
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 12) Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in your browser.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 13) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 14) The page will reload when you make changes.\
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 15) You may also see any lint errors in the console.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 16) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 17) ### `npm test`
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 18) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 19) Launches the test runner in the interactive watch mode.\
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 20) See the section about [running tests](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/running-tests) for more information.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 21) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 22) ### `npm run build`
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 23) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 24) Builds the app for production to the `build` folder.\
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 25) It correctly bundles React in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 26) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 27) The build is minified and the filenames include the hashes.\
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 28) Your app is ready to be deployed!
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 29) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 30) See the section about [deployment](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/deployment) for more information.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 31) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 32) ### `npm run eject`
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 33) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 34) **Note: this is a one-way operation. Once you `eject`, you can't go back!**
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 35) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 36) If you aren't satisfied with the build tool and configuration choices, you can `eject` at any time. This command will remove the single build dependency from your project.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 37) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 38) Instead, it will copy all the configuration files and the transitive dependencies (webpack, Babel, ESLint, etc) right into your project so you have full control over them. All of the commands except `eject` will still work, but they will point to the copied scripts so you can tweak them. At this point you're on your own.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 39) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 40) You don't have to ever use `eject`. The curated feature set is suitable for small and middle deployments, and you shouldn't feel obligated to use this feature. However we understand that this tool wouldn't be useful if you couldn't customize it when you are ready for it.
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 41)

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  76) const DraggablePartList = ({ parts, setParts }) => {
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  77)   const handleDragEnd = (event) => {
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  78)     const { active, over } = event;
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  79)     if (active.id !== over.id) {

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  85)

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  87)     setParts((prev) => prev.map((p) => (p.id === id ? updatedItem : p)));
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  88)   };
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  89) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  90)   const handleDelete = (id) => {

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  93) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  94)   return (

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  7) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  8)   const generatePages = () => {

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 10)

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 12)       // Total sedikit, tampil semua
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 13)       for (let i = 1; i <= total; i++) pages.push(i);
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 14)     } else {
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 15)       const half = Math.floor(maxPagesToShow / 2);

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 22)         end = maxPagesToShow;
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 23)       }
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 24) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 25)       // Jika di akhir

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 28)         end = total;

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 30) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 31)       // Push nomor

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 33) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 34)       // Tambah titik-titik jika perlu

===== src/hooks/useMediaQuery.js =====
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  1) // src/hooks/useMediaQuery.js
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  2)

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  4) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  5) const useMediaQuery = (query) => {
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  6)   const [matches, setMatches] = useState(() =>
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  7)     typeof window !== "undefined" ? window.matchMedia(query).matches : false
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  8)   );
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700  9) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 10)   useEffect(() => {
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 11)     const media = window.matchMedia(query);
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 12)     const listener = () => setMatches(media.matches);
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 13) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 14)     media.addEventListener("change", listener);
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 15)     return () => media.removeEventListener("change", listener);
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 16)   }, [query]);
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 17) 
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 18)   return matches;
^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 19) };

^b83dde5 (River Stewart 2025-07-16 10:49:24 -0700 21) export default useMediaQuery;
